THE CONVENTIONAL LANDING GEAR EQUIPPED AIRPLANE WAS SUBSTANTIALLY 
DAMAGED WHEN IT NOSED DOWN AFTER GROUND LOOPING DURING A LANDING 
ATTEMPT. VMC PREVAILED AND A 90 DEGREE RIGHT CROSSWIND, BLOWING AT 12 
KNOTS, WAS PRESENT. THE PILOT RELATES IN HIS STATEMENT THAT AFTER 
TOUCHDOWN THE AIRPLANE TURNED RIGHT AND THE LEFT WING WENT DOWN. 
THE AIRPLANE NOSED DOWN WHEN THE MAIN LANDING GEAR LEFT THE RUNWAY. 
